#Text=Edward
#Text=Martin ( Queens ' )
#Text=Edward Martin
#Text=, D.D. ( died 1662 ) was an English clergyman , ejected President of Queens ' College , Cambridge , and at the end of his life Dean of Ely .
#Text=Life
#Text=A native of Cambridgeshire , he matriculated in the university of Cambridge , as a sizar of Queens ' College , 5 July 1605 .
#Text=He graduated B.A. in 1608-9 , M. A. in 1612 , was elected a Fellow of his college 11 March 1617 , and proceeded B.D. in 1621 . [ 1 ]

#Text=In 1627 he was chaplain to Archbishop William Laud , and he offended the Puritan party by licensing a book by Thomas Jackson , called An Historical Narration , and also by preaching a sermon at St. Paul 's Cross against Presbyterianism .
#Text=He became vicar of Oakington in 1626 and rector of Conington , Cambridgeshire , in 1630 .
#Text=He was elected President of Queens ' College 16 October 1631 , being in the same year created D.D. by royal mandate .
#Text=He was also rector of the Church of St Peter and St Paul , Uppingham , Rutland , from 1631 to 1637 , where he was succeeded by Jeremy Taylor .
#Text=In 1638 he was instituted to the rectory of Houghton Conquest , Bedfordshire , and soon afterwards to that of Doddington , Cambridgeshire .
#Text=In August 1642 he sent the college plate to the king .
#Text=Oliver Cromwell

#Text=thereupon surrounded several colleges with soldiers , and took away by force the masters of Queens ' , Jesus College , and St. John 's College , and hurrying them to London , incarcerated them in the Tower of London by order of parliament .
#Text=Martin was afterwards removed to Lord Petre ' s house in Aldersgate Street , where he drew up the mock petition , entitled his Submission to the Covenant .
#Text=Subsequently he was remanded to Ely House and other places of confinement for more than five years .
#Text=In the meanwhile he was ejected from the presidency of Queens ' College , and lost all his other preferments .
#Text=About August 1648 he effected his escape , and went to Thorington , Suffolk , where he resided with Henry Cooke , who had been a member of his college .

#Text=He assumed the name of Matthews , but was discovered by some soldiers from Yarmouth , was brought to London , and on 23 May 1650 was committed to the Gatehouse Prison by John Bradshaw , president of the council of state .
#Text=Ultimately , by some interest with Colonel Wanton , he obtained his release and a pardon for breaking prison .

#Text=He then returned to Suffolk and resumed his own name ; but subsequently he went abroad for seven or eight years , during most of which time he lived at Paris with Christopher Hatton , 1st Baron Hatton .
#Text=In 1656 he was resident at Utrecht with many other royalists .
#Text=Returning to England at the Restoration , he was formally restored to the presidency of Queens ' College , on 2 August 1660 .
#Text=He was one of the managers of the Savoy Conference .
#Text=In February . 1662 he was nominated to the deanery of Ely , and was installed by proxy , 25 April 1662 .
#Text=He died three days afterwards on 28 April 1662 , and was buried in the college chapel .
